It allows incompatible interfaces to work together by wrapping the existing class
with a new interface.

purpose
=> to convert the interface of a class into another interface that a client expects

Components:
	1.	Target Interface: The interface that the client expects.
	2.	Adaptee: The existing class that needs to be adapted.
	3.	Adapter: The class that implements the target interface and translates calls to the adaptee.
	4.	Client: The system that interacts with the adapter using the target interface.



